setPredefinedParameter

protected void setPredefinedParameter(int index,
                                      java.lang.Object object)
Set a predefined parameter to a new value. After doing so, the textual representation of it is refreshed. This method also makes sure any generator or array element generator set for the parameter is removed.

Parameters:
index - The index of the parameter to replace.
object - The new object that will be taken as a parameter.

setGeneratorProvider

protected void setGeneratorProvider(int index,
                                    GeneratorProvider generatorProvider)
Set a parameter to be generated by an variable generator provided by the supplied. generator provider. After doing so, the textual representation of it is refreshed. This method also makes sure any predefined value or variable generator set for the parameter is removed.

Parameters:
index - The index of the parameter to replace.
generatorProvider - The generator provider that will generate values for this parameter.

setArrayElementsGeneratorProvider

protected void setArrayElementsGeneratorProvider(int index,
                                                 ArrayElementsGeneratorProvider generatorProvider)
Set a parameter to be generated by the built-in array generator which will have its values generated by the generator provided by the supplied array elements generator provider. After doing so, the textual representation of it is refreshed. This method also makes sure any predefined value or variable generator set for the parameter is removed.

Parameters:
index - The index of the parameter to replace.
generatorProvider - The generator provider that will generate the array elements.
